# Schema contract rules

- `@tell/schema` is the single source of truth for cross-package data shapes.
- Edit schemas before changing capture, detectors, taste, redesign, MCP, or web API code.
- Export inferred TS types from zod; consumers import types, never duplicate shapes.
- Parse at every boundary: MCP tools, API routes, file reads, model JSON responses.
- Schema changes are a merge gate — freeze before parallel subagent work.
- Prefer additive changes; breaking renames require updating all packages in one pass.

## Core types

`CapturePayload`, `DesignFingerprint`, `Finding`, `TasteVerdict`, `ArtDirection`, `RedesignProposal`, `TellReport`

## DoD

- `pnpm -F @tell/schema build` passes
- Downstream packages typecheck without loose `any` at boundaries
